Cows are the most common type of large domesticated ungulates. Cattle are commonly raised as livestock for meat (beef or veal, see beef cattle), for milk (see dairy cattle), and for hides, which are used to make leather. They are used as riding animals and draft animals (oxen or bullocks, which pull carts, plows and other implements). Another product of cattle is dung, which can be used to create manure or fuel. In some regions, such as parts of India, cattle have significant religious meaning. Cattle, mostly small breeds such as the Miniature Zebu, are also kept as pets.

Cockatoos are popular birds in aviculture, but their needs are difficult to meet. The cockatiel is the easiest cockatoo species to maintain and is by far the most frequently kept in captivity. They require daylight to find their food. They are not early risers, instead waiting until the sun has warmed their roosting sites before feeding. All species are generally highly social and roost, forage and travel in colourful and noisy flocks.

Dimethyl fumarate is an anti-inflammatory medication. It is used to treat relapsing-remitting forms (course of disease where symptoms flare up from time to time) of multiple sclerosis (MS; a condition in which the nerves do not function properly and people may experience weakness, numbness, loss of muscle coordination, and problems with vision, speech). It is also being investigated for the treatment of psoriasis.

Domestic pigs are raised, among other livestock; material that are garnered include their meat (known as pork), leather, certain bristles and bones that are made into brushes. You can treat them without seeing your GP. You can buy medicine for threadworms from pharmacies. This is usually a chewable tablet or liquid you swallow.

Polyester is a category of polymers that contains the ester functional group in every repeat unit of their main chain. Polyester is a man-made fibre. Polyester is very durable: resistant to most chemicals, stretching and shrinking, wrinkle resistant, mildew and abrasion-resistant. Polyester is hydrophobic in nature and quick drying. Industrial polyester fibers, yarns, and ropes are used in tire reinforcements, fabrics for conveyor belts, safety belts, coated fabrics and plastic reinforcements with high-energy absorption. Polyester fiber is used as cushioning and insulating material in pillows, comforters and upholstery padding.

Snakes are elongated, legless, carnivorous reptiles. Many species of snakes have skulls with several more joints than their lizard ancestors, enabling them to swallow prey much larger than their heads with their highly mobile jaws. Most species are nonvenomous and those that have venom use it primarily to kill and subdue prey rather than for self-defense.

Is a tapeworm that infects domestical animals and humans. In humans, infection is called sparganosis and involves larvae in the small intestines, known as spargana. The long larvae may be directly ingested by humans or may enter intermediate hosts which include frogs, birds, snakes, rats, and mice. Although humans can get infected with this parasite, they cannot complete the infected stage or grow. People cannot get infected by ingesting eggs, which are shed into the water by the shedding. If the meat of an intermediate host, such as chicken, is undercooked and it happens to be contaminated with the spargana larvae, the person can ingest it. A way to determine if an animal is infected with a type of tapeworm is to see white segments or faeces in the faeces.
